    "Body": " At Metal Pay, we are shaping digital money and revolutionizing the way people transact monetarily by reaching out to consumers new to cryptocurrency in a fun and novel way. We launched Metal Pay--a blockchain-based P2P payments app that rewards you in cryptocurrency when you send or receive money--in 2018. You can buy and sell over 30 cryptocurrencies, make payments, grow your savings, access traditional financial services and more, all from the Metal Pay app. Plus you can earn MTL, our native currency. We continue to innovate blockchain technologies and launch cryptocurrency products as we grow. Come join us and help change the financial world!Responsibilities Identify and report suspicious activity to the relevant authorities in US and EU. Review daily escalations and alerts L1 and L2 on monitoring systems. Conduct independent investigations, summarizing and presenting finding to leadership. Draft Suspicious Activity Reports (\u201cSARs\u201d) based on reviews related to system generated alerts as well as internal and external referrals. Assist in compliance cross-functional initiatives to continuously enhance our processes, while balancing the need to support a growing business/product suite and performing within our regulatory compliance obligations. Assist Compliance leadership in providing technical regulatory guidance and training on BSA/AML, OFAC Sanctions and related compliance subjects to the Metal team. Ensure all SARS/STRs, OFAC and 314(a) checks and reports are completed by the deadline. Review any AML / OFAC alerts, suspicious blockchain patterns and conduct appropriate investigations and make a determination on the disposition of the alert. Become a subject matter expert in the operation of the AML system and controls, and maintain a working understanding of applicable laws and regulations to ensure compliance. Prepare reports on BSA/AML/OFAC issues as requested by leadership. Assist in providing reports and documentation for SARs, Audits, Regulatory Exams and management. Assist the leadership in creating, enhancing and implementing the policies & procedures. Ensure compliance by the Company, its subsidiaries and vendors with the BSA/AML/Sanctions Compliance Program. Perform daily review, monitoring, and analysis of various reports, logs, and transaction data to identify trends, unusual activity, and monitor large currency activity determines if transactions are suspicious in nature such as kiting, significant changes in balances, cash structuring in deposits, loan payments, and certificates of deposit purchases, wire or ACH transfers, monetary instrument sales, new account openings, etc. Required Knowledge, Skill, and Experience Minimum 3 years of experience in crypto, financial and/or compliance related functions You are CAMS certified. If not currently certified, you would take the exam as soon as possible. Continued employment in this role would be dependent on passing exam. Experience working on various BSA/AML and OFAC Sanctions remediation projects, designing customer due diligence programs, working on transaction monitoring system implementation and rule design, Experience in developing documentation for transaction monitoring and watchlist screening Experience in developing and administering internal controls and processes; closing internal & external audit findings. Guide and train across different lines of defense while maintaining professionalism and a shared goal of quality growth. Ability to work collaboratively across a broad range of business functions, particularly senior management. Strong written, verbal and analytical skills: strong communication and presentation skills with the ability to articulate complex problems and solutions through crisp and clear messagingPreferred (but not required) Qualifications Experience with various international regulatory payments laws, including Money Transmitter/Money Service Business regulations (US). Exposure or an interest in learning regulatory requirements involving eMoney regulations (EU), MSB, FinCEN, MTL, Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Sanctions (e.g., OFAC) regulations. Additional professional compliance, or financial qualification, and membership of a recognized professional body, would be advantageous.What We Offer An exciting workplace with an inspirational team that fosters knowledge and values trust The opportunity to work on a product that will change the world Paid medical, dental, and vision benefits Paid life and LTD insurance Flexible Health Savings account 401(k) plan with company match Monthly subsidies for gym and commuter transit Learning and Development stipend Free lunches, snacks Flexible PTO and paid holidays Metal is proud to be an equal employment opportunity employer that values diversity in hiring, and gives consideration to all candidates regardless of their race, age, creed, color, religion or religious belief, national origin or ancestry, disability, military or veteran status, genetic information, sex, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, pregnancy, or any other characteristic protected by local, state, or federal law. Pursuant to the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance and other similar state laws and local ordinances, Metal will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records. ", 
